This scalping strategy is designed for trading the Nasdaq futures (NQ) using a trend-pullback approach. The system combines a 100-period EMA trend filter with RSI momentum confirmation to identify high-probability entries during pullbacks toward the moving average. Trades are executed when price aligns with the trend and momentum conditions are met. Risk management is handled automatically using ATR-based stop losses and profit targets, with optional session filtering and time-based exits to better suit intraday scalping conditions. The strategy includes fully defined entries and exits so results can be analyzed directly in TradingView’s Strategy Tester.
